\&\f(CW\*(C`uuencode\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`uuidgen\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`vconfig\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`vi\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`vlock\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`vmstat\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`volname\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`w\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`wall\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`watch\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`watchdog\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`wc\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`wget\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`which\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`who\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`whoami\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`whois\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`xargs\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`xxd\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`xz\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`yes\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`zcip\*(C'\fR
.SH "COMMAND DESCRIPTIONS"
.IX Header "COMMAND DESCRIPTIONS"
.SS acpid
.IX Subsection "acpid"
acpid [\-df] [\-c CONFDIR] [\-l LOGFILE] [\-a ACTIONFILE] [\-M MAPFILE] [\-e PROC_EVENT_FILE] [\-p PIDFILE]
.PP
Listen to ACPI events and spawn specific helpers on event arrival
.PP
.Vb 8
\&        \-d      Log to stderr, not log file (implies \-f)
\&        \-f      Run in foreground
\&        \-c DIR  Config directory [/etc/acpi]
\&        \-e FILE /proc event file [/proc/acpi/event]
\&        \-l FILE Log file [/var/log/acpid.log]
\&        \-p FILE Pid file [/var/run/acpid.pid]
\&        \-a FILE Action file [/etc/acpid.conf]
\&        \-M FILE Map file [/etc/acpi.map]
.Ve
.PP
Accept and ignore compatibility options \-g \-m \-s \-S \-v
.SS add\-shell
.IX Subsection "add-shell"
add\-shell SHELL...
.PP
Add SHELLs to /etc/shells
.SS addgroup
.IX Subsection "addgroup"
addgroup [\-g GID] [\-S] [USER] GROUP
.PP
Add a group or add a user to a group
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        \-g GID  Group id
\&        \-S      Create a system group
.Ve
.SS adduser
.IX Subsection "adduser"
adduser [OPTIONS] USER [GROUP]
.PP
Create new user, or add USER to GROUP
.PP
.Vb 9
\&        \-h DIR          Home directory
\&        \-g GECOS        GECOS field
\&        \-s SHELL        Login shell
\&        \-G GRP          Group
\&        \-S              Create a system user
\&        \-D              Don\*(Aqt assign a password
\&        \-H              Don\*(Aqt create home directory
\&        \-u UID          User id
\&        \-k SKEL         Skeleton directory (/etc/skel)
.Ve
.SS adjtimex
.IX Subsection "adjtimex"
adjtimex [\-q] [\-o OFS] [\-f FREQ] [\-p TCONST] [\-t TICK]
.PP
Read or set kernel time variables. See \fBadjtimex\fR\|(2)
.PP
.Vb 6
\&        \-q      Quiet
\&        \-o OFF  Time offset, microseconds
\&        \-f FREQ Frequency adjust, integer kernel units (65536 is 1ppm)
\&        \-t TICK Microseconds per tick, usually 10000
\&                (positive \-t or \-f values make clock run faster)
\&        \-p TCONST
.Ve
.SS ar
.IX Subsection "ar"
ar x|p|t|r [\-ov] ARCHIVE [FILE]...
.PP
Extract or list FILEs from an ar archive, or create it
.PP
.Vb 6
\&        x       Extract
\&        p       Extract to stdout
\&        t       List
\&        r       Create
\&        \-o      Restore mtime
\&        \-v      Verbose
.Ve
.SS arch
.IX Subsection "arch"
arch
.PP
Print system architecture
.SS arp
.IX Subsection "arp"
arp 
[\-vn]	[\-H HWTYPE] [\-i IF] \-a [HOSTNAME]
[\-v]		    [\-i IF] \-d HOSTNAME [pub]
[\-v]	[\-H HWTYPE] [\-i IF] \-s HOSTNAME HWADDR [temp]
[\-v]	[\-H HWTYPE] [\-i IF] \-s HOSTNAME HWADDR [netmask MASK] pub
[\-v]	[\-H HWTYPE] [\-i IF] \-Ds HOSTNAME IFACE [netmask MASK] pub
.PP
Manipulate ARP cache
.PP
.Vb 9
\&        \-a              Display (all) hosts
\&        \-d              Delete ARP entry
\&        \-s              Set new entry
\&        \-v              Verbose
\&        \-n              Don\*(Aqt resolve names
\&        \-i IF           Network interface
\&        \-D              Read HWADDR from IFACE
\&        \-A,\-p AF        Protocol family
\&        \-H HWTYPE       Hardware address type
.Ve
.SS arping
.IX Subsection "arping"
arping [\-fqbDUA] [\-c CNT] [\-w TIMEOUT] [\-I IFACE] [\-s SRC_IP] DST_IP
.PP
Send ARP requests/replies
.PP
.Vb 11
\&        \-f              Quit on first ARP reply
\&        \-q              Quiet
\&        \-b              Keep broadcasting, don\*(Aqt go unicast
\&        \-D              Exit with 1 if DST_IP replies
\&        \-U              Unsolicited ARP mode, update your neighbors
\&        \-A              ARP answer mode, update your neighbors
\&        \-c N            Stop after sending N ARP requests
\&        \-w TIMEOUT      Seconds to wait for ARP reply
\&        \-I IFACE        Interface to use (default eth0)
\&        \-s SRC_IP       Sender IP address
\&        DST_IP          Target IP address
.Ve
.SS awk
.IX Subsection "awk"
awk [OPTIONS] [AWK_PROGRAM] [FILE]...
.PP
.Vb 4
\&        \-v VAR=VAL      Set variable
\&        \-F SEP          Use SEP as field separator
\&        \-f/\-E FILE      Read program from FILE
\&        \-e AWK_PROGRAM
.Ve
.SS base32
.IX Subsection "base32"
base32 [\-d] [\-w COL] [FILE]
.PP
Base32 encode or decode FILE to standard output
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        \-d      Decode data
\&        \-w COL  Wrap lines at COL (default 76, 0 disables)
.Ve
.SS base64
.IX Subsection "base64"
base64 [\-d] [\-w COL] [FILE]
.PP
Base64 encode or decode FILE to standard output
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        \-d      Decode data
\&        \-w COL  Wrap lines at COL (default 76, 0 disables)
.Ve
.SS basename
.IX Subsection "basename"
basename FILE [SUFFIX] | \-a FILE... | \-s SUFFIX FILE...
.PP
Strip directory path and SUFFIX from FILE
.PP
.Vb 2
\&        \-a              All arguments are FILEs
\&        \-s SUFFIX       Remove SUFFIX (implies \-a)
.Ve
.SS bbconfig
.IX Subsection "bbconfig"
bbconfig
.PP
Print the config file used by busybox build
.SS bc
.IX Subsection "bc"
bc [\-sqlw] [FILE]...
.PP
Arbitrary precision calculator
.PP
.Vb 4
\&        \-q      Quiet
\&        \-l      Load standard library
\&        \-s      Be POSIX compatible
\&        \-w      Warn if extensions are used
.Ve
.PP
\&\f(CW$BC_LINE_LENGTH\fR changes output width
.SS beep
.IX Subsection "beep"
beep \-f FREQ \-l LEN \-d DELAY \-r COUNT \-n
.PP
.Vb 5
\&        \-f      Frequency in Hz
\&        \-l      Length in ms
\&        \-d      Delay in ms
\&        \-r      Repetitions
\&        \-n      Start new tone
.Ve
.SS blkdiscard
.IX Subsection "blkdiscard"
blkdiscard [\-o OFS] [\-l LEN] [\-s] DEVICE
.PP
Discard sectors on DEVICE
.PP
.Vb 3
\&        \-o OFS  Byte offset into device
\&        \-l LEN  Number of bytes to discard
\&        \-s      Perform a secure discard
.Ve
.SS blkid
.IX Subsection "blkid"
blkid [BLOCKDEV]...
.PP
Print UUIDs of all filesystems
.SS blockdev
.IX Subsection "blockdev"
blockdev OPTION BLOCKDEV
.PP
.Vb 12
\&        \-\-setro         Set ro
\&        \-\-setrw         Set rw
\&        \-\-getro         Get ro
\&        \-\-getss         Get sector size
\&        \-\-getbsz        Get block size
\&        \-\-setbsz BYTES  Set block size
\&        \-\-getsz         Get device size in 512\-byte sectors
\&        \-\-getsize64     Get device size in bytes
\&        \-\-getra         Get readahead in 512\-byte sectors
\&        \-\-setra SECTORS Set readahead
\&        \-\-flushbufs     Flush buffers
\&        \-\-rereadpt      Reread partition table
.Ve
.SS bootchartd
.IX Subsection "bootchartd"
bootchartd start [PROG ARGS]|stop|init
.PP
Create /var/log/bootchart.tgz with boot chart data
.PP
start: start background logging; with PROG, run PROG, then kill logging with USR1
stop: send USR1 to all bootchartd processes
init: start background logging; stop when getty/xdm is seen (for init scripts)
Under PID 1: as init, then exec \f(CW$bootchart_init\fR, /init, /sbin/init
.SS brctl
.IX Subsection "brctl"
brctl COMMAND [BRIDGE [ARGS]]
.PP
Manage ethernet bridges
Commands:
.PP
.Vb 10
\&        show [BRIDGE]...        Show bridges
\&        addbr BRIDGE            Create BRIDGE
\&        delbr BRIDGE            Delete BRIDGE
\&        addif BRIDGE IFACE      Add IFACE to BRIDGE
\&        delif BRIDGE IFACE      Delete IFACE from BRIDGE
\&        showmacs BRIDGE                 List MAC addresses
\&        showstp BRIDGE                  Show STP info
\&        stp BRIDGE 1/yes/on|0/no/off    Set STP on/off
\&        setageing BRIDGE SECONDS        Set ageing time
\&        setfd BRIDGE SECONDS            Set bridge forward delay
\&        sethello BRIDGE SECONDS         Set hello time
\&        setmaxage BRIDGE SECONDS        Set max message age
\&        setbridgeprio BRIDGE PRIO       Set bridge priority
\&        setportprio BRIDGE IFACE PRIO   Set port priority
\&        setpathcost BRIDGE IFACE COST   Set path cost
.Ve
.SS bunzip2
.IX Subsection "bunzip2"
bunzip2 [\-cfk] [FILE]...
.PP
Decompress FILEs (or stdin)
.PP
.Vb 4
\&        \-c      Write to stdout
\&        \-f      Force
\&        \-k      Keep input files
\&        \-t      Test integrity
.Ve
.SS bzcat
.IX Subsection "bzcat"
bzcat [FILE]...
.PP
Decompress to stdout
.SS bzip2
.IX Subsection "bzip2"
bzip2 [\-cfkdt123456789] [FILE]...
.PP
Compress FILEs (or stdin) with bzip2 algorithm
.PP
.Vb 6
\&        \-1..9   Compression level
\&        \-d      Decompress
\&        \-c      Write to stdout
\&        \-f      Force
\&        \-k      Keep input files
\&        \-t      Test integrity
.Ve
.SS cal
.IX Subsection "cal"
cal [\-jmy] [[MONTH] YEAR]
.PP
Display a calendar
.PP
.Vb 3
\&        \-j      Use julian dates
\&        \-m      Week starts on Monday
\&        \-y      Display the entire year
.Ve
.SS cat
.IX Subsection "cat"
cat [\-nbvteA] [FILE]...
.PP
Print FILEs to stdout
.PP
.Vb 6
\&        \-n      Number output lines
\&        \-b      Number nonempty lines
\&        \-v      Show nonprinting characters as ^x or M\-x
\&        \-t      ...and tabs as ^I
\&        \-e      ...and end lines with $
\&        \-A      Same as \-vte
.Ve
.SS chat
.IX Subsection "chat"
chat EXPECT [SEND [EXPECT [SEND]]...]
.PP
Useful for interacting with a modem connected to stdin/stdout.
A script consists of "expect\-send" argument pairs.
Example:
.PP
chat \*(Aq\*(Aq ATZ OK ATD123456 CONNECT \*(Aq\*(Aq ogin: pppuser word: ppppass \*(Aq~\*(Aq
.SS chattr
.IX Subsection "chattr"
chattr [\-R] [\-v VERSION] [\-p PROJID] [\-+=AacDdijsStTu] FILE...
.PP
Change ext2 file attributes
.PP
.Vb 4
\&        \-R      Recurse
\&        \-v NUM  Set version/generation number
\&        \-p NUM  Set project number
\&Modifiers:
\&
\&        \-,+,=   Remove/add/set attributes
\&Attributes:
\&
\&        A       No atime
\&        a       Append only
\&        C       No copy\-on\-write
\&        c       Compressed
\&        D       Synchronous dir updates
\&        d       Don\*(Aqt backup with dump
\&        E       Encrypted
\&        e       File uses extents
\&        F       Case\-insensitive dir
\&        I       Indexed dir
\&        i       Immutable
\&        j       Write data to journal first
\&        N       File is stored in inode
\&        P       Hierarchical project ID dir
\&        S       Synchronous file updates
\&        s       Zero storage when deleted
\&        T       Top of dir hierarchy
\&        t       Don\*(Aqt tail\-merge with other files
\&        u       Allow undelete
\&        V       Verity
.Ve
.SS chgrp
.IX Subsection "chgrp"
chgrp [\-RhLHPcvf]... GROUP FILE...
.PP
Change the group membership of FILEs to GROUP
.PP
.Vb 8
\&        \-h      Affect symlinks instead of symlink targets
\&        \-L      Traverse all symlinks to directories
\&        \-H      Traverse symlinks on command line only
\&        \-P      Don\*(Aqt traverse symlinks (default)
\&        \-R      Recurse
\&        \-c      List changed files
\&        \-v      Verbose
\&        \-f      Hide errors
.Ve
.SS chmod
.IX Subsection "chmod"
chmod [\-Rcvf] MODE[,MODE]... FILE...
.PP
MODE is octal number (bit pattern sstrwxrwxrwx) or [ugoa]{+|\-|=}[rwxXst]
.PP
.Vb 4
\&        \-R      Recurse
\&        \-c      List changed files
\&        \-v      Verbose
\&        \-f      Hide errors
.Ve
.SS chown
.IX Subsection "chown"
chown [\-RhLHPcvf]... USER[:[GRP]] FILE...
.PP
Change the owner and/or group of FILEs to USER and/or GRP
.PP
.Vb 8
\&        \-h      Affect symlinks instead of symlink targets
\&        \-L      Traverse all symlinks to directories
\&        \-H      Traverse symlinks on command line only
\&        \-P      Don\*(Aqt traverse symlinks (default)
\&        \-R      Recurse
\&        \-c      List changed files
\&        \-v      Verbose
\&        \-f      Hide errors
.Ve
.SS chpasswd
.IX Subsection "chpasswd"
chpasswd [\-me] [\-c ALG] [\-R DIR]
.PP
Read user:password from stdin and update /etc/passwd
.PP
.Vb 4
\&        \-e      Supplied passwords are in encrypted form
\&        \-m      Encrypt using md5, not des
\&        \-c ALG  des,md5,sha256/512,yescrypt (default des)
\&        \-R DIR  Directory to chroot into
.Ve
.SS chpst
.IX Subsection "chpst"
chpst [\-vP012] [\-u USER[:GRP]] [\-U USER[:GRP]] [\-e DIR]
	[\-/ DIR] [\-n NICE] [\-m BYTES] [\-d BYTES] [\-o N]
	[\-p N] [\-f BYTES] [\-c BYTES] PROG ARGS
.PP
Change the process state, run PROG
.PP
.Vb 10
\&        \-u USER[:GRP]   Set uid and gid
\&        \-U USER[:GRP]   Set $UID and $GID in environment
\&        \-e DIR          Set environment variables as specified by files
\&                        in DIR: file=1st_line_of_file
\&        \-/ DIR          Chroot to DIR
\&        \-n NICE         Add NICE to nice value
\&        \-m BYTES        Same as \-d BYTES \-s BYTES \-l BYTES
\&        \-d BYTES        Limit data segment
\&        \-o N            Limit number of open files per process
\&        \-p N            Limit number of processes per uid
\&        \-f BYTES        Limit output file sizes
\&        \-c BYTES        Limit core file size
\&        \-v              Verbose
\&        \-P              Create new process group
\&        \-0              Close stdin
\&        \-1              Close stdout
\&        \-2              Close stderr
.Ve
.SS chroot
.IX Subsection "chroot"
chroot NEWROOT [PROG ARGS]
.PP
Run PROG with root directory set to NEWROOT
.SS chrt
.IX Subsection "chrt"
chrt \-m | [\-rfobi] { \-p [PRIO] PID | PRIO PROG ARGS }
.PP
Change scheduling priority and class (default RR) for a process
.PP
.Vb 7
\&        \-m      Show min/max priorities
\&        \-p      Operate on PID
\&        \-r      Set SCHED_RR class
\&        \-f      Set SCHED_FIFO class
\&        \-o      Set SCHED_OTHER class
\&        \-b      Set SCHED_BATCH class
\&        \-i      Set SCHED_IDLE class
.Ve
.SS chvt
.IX Subsection "chvt"
chvt N
.PP
Change the foreground virtual terminal to /dev/ttyN
.SS cksum
.IX Subsection "cksum"
cksum FILE...
.PP
Calculate CRC32 checksum of FILEs
.SS clear
.IX Subsection "clear"
clear
.PP
Clear screen
.SS cmp
.IX Subsection "cmp"
cmp [\-l|s] [\-n NUM] FILE1 [FILE2 [SKIP1 [SKIP2]]]
.PP
Compare FILE1 with FILE2 (or stdin)
.PP
.Vb 4
\&        \-l      Show decimal offset and octal byte value for differing bytes,
\&                don\*(Aqt stop on first mismatch
\&        \-s      Quiet
\&        \-n NUM  Compare at most NUM bytes
.Ve
.SS comm
.IX Subsection "comm"
comm [\-123] FILE1 FILE2
.PP
Compare FILE1 with FILE2
.PP
.Vb 3
\&        \-1      Suppress lines unique to FILE1
\&        \-2      Suppress lines unique to FILE2
\&        \-3      Suppress lines common to both files
.Ve
.SS conspy
.IX Subsection "conspy"
conspy [\-vcsndfFQ] [\-x COL] [\-y LINE] [CONSOLE_NO]
.PP
A text\-mode VNC like program for Linux virtual consoles.
To exit, quickly press ESC 3 times.
.PP
.Vb 10
\&        \-v      Don\*(Aqt send keystrokes to the console
\&        \-c      Create missing /dev/{tty,vcsa}N
\&        \-s      Open a SHELL session
\&        \-n      Black & white
\&        \-d      Dump console to stdout
\&        \-f      Follow cursor
\&        \-F      Assume console is on a framebuffer device
\&        \-Q      Disable exit on ESC\-ESC\-ESC
\&        \-x COL  Starting column
\&        \-y LINE Starting line
.Ve
.SS cp
.IX Subsection "cp"
cp [\-arPLHpfinlsTu] SOURCE DEST
or: cp [\-arPLHpfinlsu] SOURCE... { \-t DIRECTORY | DIRECTORY }
.PP
Copy SOURCEs to DEST
.PP
.Vb 10
\&        \-a      Same as \-dpR
\&        \-R,\-r   Recurse
\&        \-d,\-P   Preserve symlinks (default if \-R)
\&        \-L      Follow all symlinks
\&        \-H      Follow symlinks on command line
\&        \-p      Preserve file attributes if possible
\&        \-f      Overwrite
\&        \-i      Prompt before overwrite
\&        \-n      Don\*(Aqt overwrite
\&        \-l,\-s   Create (sym)links
\&        \-T      Refuse to copy if DEST is a directory
\&        \-t DIR  Copy all SOURCEs into DIR
\&        \-u      Copy only newer files
.Ve
.SS cpio
.IX Subsection "cpio"
cpio [\-dmvu] [\-F FILE] [\-R USER[:GRP]] [\-H newc] [\-tio] [\-p DIR] [EXTR_FILE]...
.PP
Extract (\-i) or list (\-t) files from a cpio archive on stdin, or
take file list from stdin and create an archive (\-o) or copy files (\-p)
.PP
Main operation mode:
.PP
.Vb 5
\&        \-t      List
\&        \-i      Extract EXTR_FILEs (or all)
\&        \-o      Create (requires \-H newc)
\&        \-p DIR  Copy files to DIR
\&Options:
\&
\&        \-H newc Archive format
\&        \-d      Make leading directories
\&        \-m      Restore mtime
\&        \-v      Verbose
\&        \-u      Overwrite
\&        \-F FILE Input (\-t,\-i,\-p) or output (\-o) file
\&        \-R USER[:GRP]   Set owner of created files
\&        \-L      Dereference symlinks
\&        \-0      NUL terminated input
\&        \-\-ignore\-devno
\&        \-\-renumber\-inodes
.Ve
.SS crc32
.IX Subsection "crc32"
crc32 FILE...
.PP
Calculate CRC32 checksum of FILEs
.SS crond
.IX Subsection "crond"
crond [\-fbS] [\-l N] [\-d N] [\-L LOGFILE] [\-c DIR]
.PP
.Vb 7
\&        \-f      Foreground
\&        \-b      Background (default)
\&        \-S      Log to syslog (default)
\&        \-l N    Set log level. Most verbose 0, default 8
\&        \-d N    Set log level, log to stderr
\&        \-L FILE Log to FILE
\&        \-c DIR  Cron dir. Default:/var/spool/cron/crontabs
.Ve
.SS crontab
.IX Subsection "crontab"
crontab [\-c DIR] [\-u USER] [\-ler]|[FILE]
.PP
.Vb 6
\&        \-c      Crontab directory
\&        \-u      User
\&        \-l      List crontab
\&        \-e      Edit crontab
\&        \-r      Delete crontab
\&        FILE    Replace crontab by FILE (\*(Aq\-\*(Aq: stdin)
.Ve
.SS cryptpw
.IX Subsection "cryptpw"
cryptpw [\-P FD] [\-m TYPE] [\-S SALT] [PASSWORD] [SALT]
.PP
Print \fBcrypt\fR\|(3) hashed PASSWORD
.PP
.Vb 3
\&        \-P N    Read password from fd N
\&        \-m TYPE des,md5,sha256/512,yescrypt (default des)
\&        \-S SALT
.Ve
.SS cttyhack
.IX Subsection "cttyhack"
cttyhack [PROG ARGS]
.PP
Give PROG a controlling tty if possible.
Example for /etc/inittab (for busybox init):
	::respawn:/bin/cttyhack /bin/sh
Giving controlling tty to shell running with PID 1:
	$ exec cttyhack sh
Starting interactive shell from boot shell script:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        setsid cttyhack sh
.Ve
.SS curl
.IX Subsection "curl"
curl [OPTIONS] URL
.PP
Fetch content from URL
.PP
.Vb 5
\&        \-X METH HTTP method
\&        \-H HDR  HTTP header
\&        \-d DATA HTTP data
\&        \-o FILE Output file
\&        \-s      Silent
.Ve
.SS cut
.IX Subsection "cut"
cut {\-b|c LIST | \-f|F LIST [\-d SEP] [\-s]} [\-D] [\-O SEP] [FILE]...
.PP
Print selected fields from FILEs to stdout
.PP
.Vb 9
\&        \-b LIST Output only bytes from LIST
\&        \-c LIST Output only characters from LIST
\&        \-d SEP  Input field delimiter (default \-f TAB, \-F run of whitespace)
\&        \-f LIST Print only these fields (\-d is single char)
\&        \-F LIST Print only these fields (\-d is regex)
\&        \-s      Drop lines with no delimiter (else print them in full)
\&        \-D      Don\*(Aqt sort ranges; line without delimiters has one field
\&        \-\-output\-delimiter SEP  Output field delimeter
\&        \-n      Ignored
.Ve
.SS date
.IX Subsection "date"
date [OPTIONS] [+FMT] [[\-s] TIME]
.PP
Display time (using +FMT), or set time
.PP
.Vb 8
\&        \-u              Work in UTC (don\*(Aqt convert to local time)
\&        [\-s] TIME       Set time to TIME
